# Pepper ROS Noetic Setup Guide

This repository contains the environment and instructions for running the **Pepper ROS** simulation within a Docker container.

## 1. Initial Setup

### Extract the Project
1. Run the following command in your terminal: docker pull ghcr.io/00ducky13/pepper_stage1_ros:latest

### Build
1. sudo docker build -t pepper_stage1_ros .

### Enable GUI support
1. xhost +local:docker

### Launch Container
sudo docker run -it \
    --env="DISPLAY" \
    --env="QT_X11_NO_MITSHM=1" \
    --volume="/tmp/.X11-unix:/tmp/.X11-unix:rw" \
    pepper_stage1_ros bash

### In container
roscore &
export LIBGL_ALWAYS_SOFTWARE=1
roslaunch <package_name> <simulation_file>.launch
